geneVariantDescriptions.description: FAT1 mutant indicates an unspecified mutation in the FAT1 gene.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a clinical study, FAT1 mutations were associated with improved durable clinical benefit (71.4% vs 22.7%, p=0.01) and objective response rate (57.1% vs 15.2%, p=0.02) compared to wild-type in non-small cell lung cancer patients treated with immunotherapies, including Tecentriq (atezolizumab) (n=5), Opdivo (nivolumab) (n=17), Keytruda (pembrolizumab) (n=36), and Camrelizumab (SHR-1210) (n=20) (PMID: 31085721).

references.title: Comprehensive Genomic Profiling Identifies Novel Genetic Predictors of Response to Anti-PD-(L)1 Therapies in Non-Small Cell Lung Cancer.
